HEADWORD: Salvability
<hw>Sal`va*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
condition of being salvable; salvableness.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the Latin scheme of redemption, <qex>salvability</qex> was not
possible outside the communion of the visible organization.</q>
<rj><qau>A. V. G. Allen.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salvable</ent>⟦br⟧
